  "active_lock_reason": null,
  "body": "### Component\r\n\r\nCast\r\n\r\n### Have you ensured that all of these are up to date?\r\n\r\n- [X] Foundry\r\n- [X] Foundryup\r\n\r\n### What version of Foundry are you on?\r\n\r\ncast 0.2.0 (9256265 2023-01-13T00:04:00.237556113Z)\r\n\r\n### What command(s) is the bug in?\r\n\r\ncast run\r\n\r\n### Operating System\r\n\r\nLinux\r\n\r\n### Describe the bug\r\n\r\nIf a contract interaction depends on `block.difficulty`, a local execution via `cast run` yields wrong results because the ~`difficulty`~ `mixHash` is not fetched from the node provider. It is `0` by default.\r\n\r\nTo reproduce see the following contract interaction: https://goerli.etherscan.io/tx/0x57c39e52c6a3a4cafa3075b171cebb299b891300f6de4a711db24e0997d0a4f9#eventlog which logged `block.difficulty` by emitting an event with data `0x8c712d4cab1b6508e03e5c5ba69d496707cd60a585dd7a33d27e34013ab783a4`.\r\nA local execution via\r\n```bash\r\ncast run 0x57c39e52c6a3a4cafa3075b171cebb299b891300f6de4a711db24e0997d0a4f9 --rpc-url $GOERLI_RPC_URL\r\n``` \r\nyields the following output\r\n```bash\r\nExecuting previous transactions from the block.\r\nTraces:\r\n  [1178] DifficultyLogger::log() \r\n    ├─ emit Difficulty(: 0)\r\n    └─ ← ()\r\n\r\n```",
